{
  "_comment": [
    "The exact ffmpeg sidecars ANVIL ships, one entry per platform target. Single source of",
    "truth for the provisioning scripts (scripts/fetch-ffmpeg.ps1 on Windows,",
    "scripts/build-ffmpeg-macos.sh on macOS); anvil_media::sidecar::FFMPEG_PINS carries the same",
    "values in code, and the unit test `pin_json_matches_the_code` fails if the two ever drift.",
    "",
    "Schema: `targets` is a map keyed by the code's runtime target string,",
    "format!(\"{}-{}\", std::env::consts::OS, std::env::consts::ARCH) -> \"windows-x86_64\",",
    "\"macos-aarch64\", \"macos-x86_64\". `forbidden_configure_markers` is shared at top level.",
    "",
    "binary_sha256 is the RAW file hash (provisioning gate: fetch/build/stage verify the vendored",
    "bytes against it). content_sha256 (macOS only) is the signing-INDEPENDENT Mach-O content hash",
    "(sig blob excluded + the three size fields it perturbs zeroed) that anvil-media enforces at RUN",
    "time: a Developer-ID re-sign rewrites the raw bytes but not the content, so a raw pin could not",
    "match the signed sidecar that actually ships. Windows/PE has no content_sha256 (stays raw until",
    "Windows signing lands). See crates/anvil-media/src/sidecar.rs macho_content_sha256 + ADR-012.",
    "",
    "ffmpeg is run as a SEPARATE PROCESS and is never linked into ANVIL, so its licence does",
    "not reach ANVIL's MIT code. But we redistribute the binary, so each build must be free of",
    "GPL components: no --enable-gpl, no --enable-nonfree, and x264/x265/xvid/fdk-aac/rubberband/",
    "vidstab/frei0r/avisynth all disabled. `ffmpeg -version` self-reports the configure line and",
    "the provisioning + `pin_json_matches_the_code` scan it against forbidden_configure_markers.",
    "",
    "windows-x86_64: BtbN's prebuilt win64-lgpl. It sets --enable-version3, so it is LGPL v3",
    "(fine for GitHub-Releases distribution, incompatible with the Apple App Store).",
    "",
    "macos-aarch64 / macos-x86_64: built from source per-arch by scripts/build-ffmpeg-macos.sh —",
    "no LGPL-clean prebuilt macOS ffmpeg exists anywhere (BtbN ships none; evermeet/osxexperts/",
    "martin-riedl/Homebrew are all GPL). These deliberately OMIT --enable-version3, so they are",
    "LGPL-2.1-or-later: stricter than the Windows pin. built-from-source entries have no archive,",
    "so they carry a `source_url` provenance string instead of a URL and no archive_* fields.",
    "See handoff/07-RISKS-LEGAL.md §2, handoff/08-MAC.md §1, and docs/licenses.md."
  ],
  "forbidden_configure_markers": [
    "gpl",
    "nonfree",
    "avisynth",
    "frei0r",
    "libcdio",
    "libdavs2",
    "libdvdnav",
    "libdvdread",
    "librubberband",
    "libvidstab",
    "libx264",
    "libx265",
    "libxavs",
    "libxavs2",
    "libxvid",
    "libsmbclient",
    "decklink",
    "libfdk_aac",
    "libmpeghdec"
  ],
